reviews.review_text:
the end is near great sounding show and set list looks good on paper, but you can hear Jerry's demise in his playing. off his game big time and it shows from the first notes of Shakedown to the last note payed of the night.
4 stars for the sound quality, but the playing is hard to listen to.
Box of Rain Box of Rain will always be my happy go to song when I feel down. Thank you for uploading.

Goodbye Jerry.  This was the last time I saw Jerry Garcia. This was also the only Grateful Dead show that my daughter Melian ever attended. She was a baby, about 6 months old. Her mother, Sandi, breast-fed her during the set break. It's a real shame that the man died trying to get clean! There will never be another man like him in this world. Thanks to Jerry my life had lots of different adventures. Because of Jerry my life changed forever. And because of Jerry I drove & saw places I never would have seen. I drove across the nation to California, stopping to see the Grand Canyon along the way. Got to see a small Redwood forest, drive across the Golden Gate Bridge & the Bay Bridge as well. Drove thru the Haight-Ashury intersection. Seen "the Palace" at Auburn Hills, seen Niagara Falls after a show at Rich Stadium. Been to Giants stadium & Knickerbocker Arena. Been as far south as Key Largo after seeing a show in Miami. My first show was in 1988 & by the time this show came around I had seen the Dead about 70 times. Jerry was a true artist in every way!!!  YOU KNOW OUR LOVE WILL NOT FADE AWAY!!!!!🌈💞🎶🎵🎶🎶🎵🎵🎶💫💥✌👍🤘👁💕💦🍭🍥🎲🎰
Rockin show Like the energy they bring to tunes like Wang Dang Doodle and Loose Lucy. Great sound. Hard to believe the end was near.
